Bradley Real Estate Trust said it signeda 99-year lease for property in downtown Minneapolis to BCEDMinnesota Inc.    The lease will increase net income by about 24 cts a shareon a post-February 1987 three-for-two stock split basis. For1986, the Trust reported net income of 1.3 mln dlrs or 38 cts ashare on a post-split basis.    Bradley will also be entitled to a one-time additionalrental payment of 30 cts a share upon BCED entering into aspace lease with a prime national tenant and a share in aportion of net cash flow from operations on the property. Reuter&#3;